FY 2026 Plans:
Develop, test, train, field, transition and sustain advanced rapid reaction capabilities in response to emergent requirements from
multiple Combatant Commands. Specifically, support development, testing, deployment and sustainment of two USSF UONs, 24-
SOC-01 and 25-CYBER-01, supporting 5 Combatant Commands. Conduct initial technical development and integration activities
against relevant threat systems and technologies in preparation for operational requirements based on operational intelligence.
Develop and test advanced prototypes in support of activities within the OSO Technology portfolio. Based on technological
advances relevant to the mission area, develop, integrate, and evaluate next generation capabilities into Government Reference
Architecture (GRA) Increment 7. Execute remote DevSecOps activities using all three remote Outside Continental United States
(OCONUS) development sites to verify system performance in the operational environment and stay abreast of emerging
technologies. Enhance fielded rapid reaction capabilities in response to evolving threats and operator feedback.

Additionally, FY 2026 funding will allow the program to enhance and refresh critical infrastructure equipment for all the remote
development sites and the local development and integration labs. Lastly, we will look to leverage commercial developmental
opportunities and international relationships, if appropriate. Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support,
studies, technical analysis, experimentation, prototyping, etc.
FY 2027 Plans:
-Develop, test, train, field, transition and sustain advanced rapid reaction capabilities in response to emergent requirements from
multiple Combatant Commands. Specifically, sustain and transition USSF UONs 24- SOC-01 and 25-CYBER-01, supporting 5
Combatant Commands through the duration of their contingency operations.
-Conduct initial technical development and integration activities against relevant threat systems and technologies in preparation
for operational requirements based on operational intelligence.
-Develop and test advanced prototypes in support of activities within the Offensive Space Operations (OSO) Technology portfolio.
-Complete development, test and fielding of capabilities into new GRA Increment 7.
-Stand up possible fourth overseas remote development site in partnership with USINDOPACOM.
-Execute remote DevSecOps activities using all three remote Outside Continental United States (OCONUS) development sites to
verify system performance in the operational environment and stay abreast of emerging technologies.
-Enhance fielded rapid reaction capabilities in response to evolving threats and operator feedback.
-Complete the tech refresh of critical infrastructure equipment for all the remote development sites and the local development and
integration labs.
-Leverage commercial developmental opportunities and international relationships, if appropriate.


