FY 2026 Plans:
Conduct technical development and integration activities against relevant threat systems and technologies in preparation for
operational requirements. This includes performing modeling, simulation, and analysis for DSO, OSO, SDA, and C2 capabilities
using the Battle Management Kill Chain (BMKC) model and other models available (e.g., FFRDC Aerospace models). The
program supports updating these models with the current threat information for SDA and C2 capabilities in performing individual
mission threads and campaign analysis.

Conduct systems engineering and mission architecture engineering activities to allow Space Force to link its individual space
defense programs to define the enterprise-level system requirements supporting the Joint warfighter. Perform intelligence
analysis and coordination to support the development of DSO, OSO, SDA, and C2 enterprise-level system requirements.
