for operational requirements. This includes modeling, simulation, and analysis for DSO, OSO, SDA, and Battle Management
Command, Control and Communications (BMC3) capabilities. The program supports updating these models with the current
threat information for SDA and BMC3 capabilities in performing individual mission threads and campaign analysis.

-Support requirements development of space enterprise kill chains integration, including the identification and assessment of risks
and gaps in the current and future space control architecture.
Provide engineering requirements and configuration management, including development of governance documents, change
management, risk management, and engineering reviews.
-Provide functional analysis support critical to determining requirements for the future space control architecture.

-Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
