B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                         FY 2025          FY 2026        FY 2027
Title: NSTTC                                                                                                                                  158.785          149.505          0.000
Description: Supports the development of the National Space Test & Training Complex (NSTTC) to deliver physical and digital
environments, systems, tools and capabilities critical for developmental and operational test, training, exercises, wargames,
and tactics development for space systems. Includes development, demonstration, and continuous delivery of test and training,
hardware and software that yield the capabilities required to test, validate, and verify performance of integrated space systems
and the Guardians that operate them. Provides a safe, secure, and realistic, relevant space-based physical and digital arena for
controlled space, ground, and cyber systems to support test and training needs. Capabilities enable Guardian and mission system
combat lethality.

Cyber Range: Provides live and simulated cyber operations and security test and training. Delivers USSF systems Verification,
Validation, and Accreditation (VV&A) to ensure cyber resiliency, security, and interoperability.

Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations Range: Provides ground-based system, range control, and on-orbit surrogate for
Electromagnetic Warfare (EW), Satellite Communications (SATCOM), and Position Navigation and Timing (PNT) test and training.

Orbital Range: Provides sensor and data fusion to enable live, on-orbit Orbital Warfare (OW) test and training. On-orbit range
system supports execution of exquisite, discrete demonstrations.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Digital Test & Training: Delivers digital environments, connectivity, and cradle-to-grave Modeling and Simulation (M&S) to enable
operational test, operator training and tactics development in US Space Force (USSF) and Joint exercises, and wargaming.
Consists of framework, applications, physical hardware, simulation, and data management needed to meet operational test and
training requirements in accordance with Space Training and Readiness Command (STARCOM) priorities.

Infrastructure: Delivers the computer, storage, data management, and connectivity backbone, at all classification levels, to
enable an integrated NSTTC framework across Space Force, Joint, and Government owned environments. Consists of facilities
support, common network infrastructure, cloud hosting, data centers, platform services and the cybersecurity required to analyze
and share data as well as integrate and distribute test and training systems. Provides access to test and training users, range
operators, range developers, integrating programs and partners systems.

Readiness: Delivers and utilizes virtual environments, connectivity, tools, and applications for USSF and Joint Exercises and
Wargames to enable Guardian advanced training and readiness to be presented to the Combatant Commands. Provides materiel
solutions to rapidly address short-term Guardian training and tactics capability gaps.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue investments in Cyber, Electromagnetic, and Orbital ranges, including foundational infrastructure development as well
as modernization and improvement of existing capabilities to keep current with military priorities, evolving threats, and advanced
training involving USSF and joint systems and operations
- Continue development of Electromagnetic Spectrum range Command, Control, and Communication (C3), terminal, data
generation systems
- Continue support to warfighting community of Electromagnetic Warfare (EW) advanced training environment
- Continue development of integrated data transport architecture across the ranges
- Continue developing digital High-End Advanced Test, Training, and Tactics Development (HEAT3) platform to enable enduring
Joint Simulation Environment (JSE)-based digital test and training architecture
- Deliver Minimum Viable Product (MVP)-level digital HEAT3 platform for initial JSE integration; deliver and integrate initial set of
intel-validated threat models, enabling HEAT3 platform to support test and training relevant to top-priority DoW threat scenario
- Continue development of advanced and combat training capabilities for exercises and wargames. Deliver MVP medium fidelity
digital capability to support evolved Space Flag requirements.
- Continue development of digital range operations via Commercial Solutions Openings (CSOs)
FY 2027 Plans:
In FY 2027, funds transferred to new Program Element 1206617SF, Project 644441 Operational Test & Training Infrastructure.
