A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Provide space warfighters with interconnected, scalable, high-fidelity and distributed physical and digital ranges for full-spectrum test and training to develop, validate,
and sharpen joint warfighting capabilities necessary to prevail and enable space superiority that is essential to achieve peace through strength.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                         FY 2025          FY 2026        FY 2027
Title: NSTTC                                                                                                                                  158.785          149.505          0.000
Description: Supports the development of the National Space Test & Training Complex (NSTTC) to deliver physical and digital
environments, systems, tools and capabilities critical for developmental and operational test, training, exercises, wargames,
and tactics development for space systems. Includes development, demonstration, and continuous delivery of test and training,
hardware and software that yield the capabilities required to test, validate, and verify performance of integrated space systems
and the Guardians that operate them. Provides a safe, secure, and realistic, relevant space-based physical and digital arena for
controlled space, ground, and cyber systems to support test and training needs. Capabilities enable Guardian and mission system
combat lethality.

Cyber Range: Provides live and simulated cyber operations and security test and training. Delivers USSF systems Verification,
Validation, and Accreditation (VV&A) to ensure cyber resiliency, security, and interoperability.

Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations Range: Provides ground-based system, range control, and on-orbit surrogate for
Electromagnetic Warfare (EW), Satellite Communications (SATCOM), and Position Navigation and Timing (PNT) test and training.

Orbital Range: Provides sensor and data fusion to enable live, on-orbit Orbital Warfare (OW) test and training. On-orbit range
system supports execution of exquisite, discrete demonstrations.




