A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This is not a New Start. FY 2025-2026 UDL funds are allocated in the Space Situation Awareness Operations (SSAO) Program Element (PE) 1203940SF and in
FY2027+ UDL funds transferred to a new Program Element (PE) 1203156SF, Project 673941, Unified Data Library (UDL).

 The UDL project (673941) supports integration, exploitation, and delivery of Space Domain Awareness (SDA) and other space-related data sources for C2 and battle
 management of space forces. It focuses on enabling data sharing, establishing the data architecture required to aggregate multi-sensor data for broader use at different
 classification levels, transforming any-source data into normalized, usable information via data exploitation tools, followed by data handoff to Battle Management
 Command and Control mission systems to support actual space operations. The UDL will directly connect to dedicated USSF collateral, contributing and non-traditional
 sensors and systems with modernized interfaces and transport options to broadly expose data. The UDL will be the single source for accessing and managing all data in
 support of the USSF, providing a central location to find and access data, enabling superior analytics.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025           FY 2026    FY 2027
Title: Unified Data Library (UDL)                                                                                                              -                 -      74.275
Description: UDL capabilities support integration, exploitation, and delivery of data sources for C2 and battle management
of space forces. UDL will continue to develop the library by on-boarding new data sets, directly connecting to SDA sensors,
expanding data services, expanding defensive cyber operations capabilities, adding non-metric data to the global data
marketplace, continuing to expand local area network capability to share Space Surveillance Network (SSN) data in a cyber-
secure manner, allowing optimized data flow for use of existing SDA capability, and providing access to new commercial SDA
innovations that will enable the broader SDA mission. The UDL enables analysis across the global space enterprise, as well as for
Space Force related exercise support, cross-domain solution services, and integration of the legacy communications architecture
with the UDL.

FY 2027 Plans:
Modernize the UDL to support a truly federated data architecture that offers enhanced scalability and flexibility for the Joint
Force and allies. This modern architecture will enable the UDL to increase the data volume and number of data sources as new
commercial sensors and systems are integrated into the SDA ecosystem. This architecture will improve data governance and
