A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This is not a New Start. In FY 2027, funds for Integrated Operations Networking (ION) are transferred from PE 1203010SF, Project 646602 to PE 1203156SF, Project
673945.

 The USSF's Integrated Operations Networking (ION) effort is a critical component of the Space Force's mission to enable the Battle Management, Command, Control,
 and Communications (BMC3) warfighter missions. ION will integrate commercially available information technology (IT) capabilities to address urgent operational
 needs and close networking gaps tied to kill chain gaps identified by Space Forces - Space operating in support of USSPACECOM. ION aims to improve tactical and
 operational timelines within the kill-chain to enable USSF's ability to deliver credible combat power effects in support of the Joint Force.

 The program will focus on developing a secure, reliable, and multi-classification transport layer to support space missions, with an emphasis on direct connection
 between all elements of force packages, establishing a special access program (SAP)-level network with overlays, and developing high-speed connectivity and high
 resilience to Commercial Cloud Services (C2S). The ION program will also pursue opportunities to leverage existing efforts, such as meshONE-T, to support the
 development of ION.

 Funding in FY 2027 will enable the program to maintain a steady pace of execution throughout the year, ensuring that the Space Force can leverage the ION capability
 to enhance its mission effectiveness. The ION program will provide a critical capability to the Space Force, enabling the service to operate in a contested environment
 and to defend against adversary operations. The program will be executed in a manner that is consistent with the Space Force's priorities, including the development of
 a digital engineering ecosystem, the implementation of zero trust capabilities, and the modernization of cryptography and supply chain risk management.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025           FY 2026    FY 2027
Title: USSF Integrated Operations Networking (ION)                                                                                              -                 -      34.822
Description: ION will provide a secure, reliable, multi-classification transport layer to support space missions. ION will be a
dynamic cloud-based software-defined mission networking gap filler that integrates Space Force capabilities providing high
bandwidth and low latency for essential capabilities including support to Artificial Intelligence (AI) and the Unified Data Library
(UDL). Space Force initiated ION to address significant mission network infrastructure technology debt and to better prepare for
a new threat environment. ION will continue to deploy a special and compartmented access program (SAP/CAP) capable Unified
Data Library within an accredited government cloud that will enable mission partners to access timely, high resolution data at all



