FY 2027 Plans:
FY 2027 efforts will focus on scaling and accelerating the expansion of classified cloud and networking infrastructure to
support secure data transport in alignment with projected threat timelines. This includes building upon the existing pathfinder
implementation to connect disparate classified space capabilities into integrated, resilient data transport network. ION will
continue to support the terrestrial network, advancing the integration of a secure, reliable, multi-classification transport layer.
This includes the incorporation of Command and Control (C2) nodes into the existing classified kill web, directly enhancing the
National Space Test and Training Complex (NSTTC). These improvements will increase classified communication resiliency, align
development activities, and expand opportunities for advanced training and testing- leveraging test and training data sources into
UDL to strengthen USSF's ability to protect and defend high-priority space missions. ION enables rapid response capabilities by
enhancing system resiliency and situational awareness—key to operating in a contested space domain. Planned activities may
include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, and prototyping.
Efforts may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and
emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
