B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
- Continue equipping Guardians in MD 2, DEL 9 and other SpOC units with analyses and tool development provided on tactically
relevant timelines, enabling SpOC operators to execute their mission. These analyses and tools focus on Space Domain
Awareness (SDA), including detecting, characterizing, attributing, predicting, and targeting activities in the space domain to inform
decision making across Missile Warning (MW), Command and Control (C2), Space Control, Orbital Warfare (OW), and other
mission areas.
- Continue to ensure that our current and future Space Domain Awareness (SDA) systems are providing accurate data through
evaluation of operational SDA sensors data and validation of SDA & C2 programs of record.
- Provide interoperable astrodynamics software for the entire SDA enterprise via the Astrodynamic Standards (AstroStds). The
AstroStds are a suite of verified and validated algorithms, designed to function like the operational Space Domain Awareness
(SDA) algorithms used by Mission Delta 2 (SPADOC, ASW, CAVENet/SMP, & ATLAS) and built for easy integration with
practically any programming language. The AstroStds libraries are currently released as no cost Government Off The Shelf
(GOTS) products to qualified DOW contractors and U.S. Government users and support a wide variety of efforts, including: DARC
(Deep Space Advanced Radar Capability), GEODSS (Ground-Based Electro-Optical Deep Space Surveillance), Space Fence,
ISSA (Integrated Solutions for Situational Awareness), projects within AFRL (Air Force Research Laboratories), and many others.
- Deliver SpOC/CC's automated SPAFORGEN Assessments Dashboard.
- Initiate annual look-back analysis of Operational Capability/System Capability rates and impacts to mission. Correlate findings
with relevant OPLANs to identify hidden risks and/or update relevant campaign analyses.
- Develop rules-based automated decision support categories of impact of OPSCAP/SYSCAP statuses to mission risk/
performance.
